<dl id="n35287e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35287e">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35287e"> 287(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> anemodoulion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>History, Architecture and Antiquities</i>.&mdash;]</font> In the forum of Theodosius I. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> was the Anemodoulion, a beautiful pyramidal structure, surmounted by a vane to indicate the direction of the wind. <small> &ldquo;CONSTANTINOPLE&rdquo; <cite a>Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
